+{"parentUuid":"8fff61f7-c172-4092-aa14-f776d66286e7","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"/workspace","sessionId":"6feb4c99-60bb-4ef2-96ec-aea7c6031654","version":"2.1.63","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"serene-wishing-hellman","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01E1565vtasv6B3AU4j4xauj","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The implementation is complete. Here's a summary of what was built:\n\n## Implementation Summary\n\n### `src/index.ts`\n\n**`solveToggle(machine: Machine): number[] | null`** - Solves the toggle puzzle over GF(2):\n1. Builds augmented matrix and performs Gaussian elimination (RREF) over GF(2)\n2. Checks consistency (returns `null` if impossible)\n3. For unique solutions (0 free vars): returns directly\n4. For ≤25 free vars: Gray code enumeration with O(1) incremental weight updates\n5. For >25 free vars: Meet-in-the-middle, grouping by pivot contribution bitmask (efficient because many free vars implies few pivots)\n\n**`solveCounter(lights, buttons, modulus): number[] | null`** - Solves the counter puzzle over GF(p):\n1. Builds augmented matrix and performs Gaussian elimination over GF(p) using modular inverse\n2. Checks consistency (returns `null` if impossible)  \n3. For unique solutions: returns directly\n4. For small search spaces (p^k ≤ 8M): odometer-style enumeration with incremental pivot updates\n5. For larger search spaces: Branch-and-bound with greedy initialization and tight pruning using determined pivot values\n\n### Key design decisions:\n- **GF(2)**: Uses BigInt bitmasks for lex comparison (comparing lowest set bit of XOR), Uint8Array for Gaussian elimination\n- **GF(p)**: Uses extended Euclidean for modular inverse, Uint8Array for pivot values (safe since p ≤ 97 < 256)\n- **Lex ordering**: Toggle uses bitmask comparison; Counter uses array lexicographic comparison\n- **Performance**: All algorithms handle 40 buttons × 40 lights/counters within 5 seconds"}],"stop_reason":"end_tu